messageBody:
Concerning the modified Roe there are two examples on page
thirteen under moor and mere. Unless Kingsley Read based the standard
form on a dialect that pronounces "ear" as /iər/.

--- In Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com, "oliver langan"
<oliverlangan@...> wrote:
>
> Which modified Roe do you mean? Can you point me to an example in
the
> QS manual? It was surely an oversight that it was not included.
>
> o
>
> --- In Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com, "tim_rice09" <tim_rice09@>
wrote:
> > Although it is missing one character, the
> > modified Roe that follows Eat and Ooze.
>
